CNCP v1 23939
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#10691: Slots in loops only assigned once when component used as custom element",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:56.685554+00:00",
  "text": "Slots in loops only assigned once when component used as custom element\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.4.21\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sawmurai/vue-custom-elements-slots-reproducer\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- Clone the repo\r\n- Run pnpm install\r\n- Build the custom element (`cd packages/vue-custom-elements && pnpm run build`)\r\n- Run the reproducer (`cd packages/vue-custom-elements-consumer && pnpm run dev`)\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nThe slot-content, rendered three times, should show the replacement, three times.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nThe slot-content, rendered three times, is only replaced once.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nSystem:\r\n    OS: Linux 6.5 Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS 22.04.3 LTS (Jammy Jellyfish)\r\n    CPU: (16) x64 AMD Ryzen 7 3800X 8-Core Processor\r\n    Memory: 56.84 GB / 62.67 GB\r\n    Container: Yes\r\n    Shell: 3.7.0 - /usr/bin/fish\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 20.12.1 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v20.12.1/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - ~/.yarn/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 10.5.0 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v20.12.1/bin/npm\r\n    pnpm: 8.15.6 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v20.12.1/bin/pnpm\r\n    bun: 1.0.0 - ~/.bun/bin/bun\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 121.0.6167.160\r\n    Chromium: 123.0.6312.86\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nI think to fix this problem the slot assignment needs to be done manually (by setting the [slotAssignment](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ShadowRoot/slotAssignment) to manual). I played with that option and was able to get a rough version working (I cloned the `<div slot=\"root\">` elements and assigned them manually to each instance of the slot in the DOM). Of course, the devil is in the details and I did not even look at edge cases. Before attempting a full-blown PR, I would like your feedback, if this is something you even want to support, first.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have",
    "scope: custom elements"
  ],
